  "prompt": "My Mother and elder brother keep fighting. What should I do to stop this?",
  "response": "Dealing with family conflicts can be challenging. Here are some suggestions to help:\n\n1. Stay neutral\n- Don't take sides\n- Listen to both perspectives without judgment\n- Avoid escalating tensions\n\n2. Communication strategies\n- Encourage calm, respectful dialogue\n- Help them understand each other's perspectives\n- Suggest they talk when emotions are not high\n\n3. Mediation\n- Offer to be a neutral mediator\n- Help them communicate more effectively\n- Focus on finding common ground\n\n4. Identify root causes\n- Try to understand why they're fighting\n- Look for underlying issues like stress, misunderstandings, or past grievances\n\n5. Suggest professional help\n- Family counseling can provide professional mediation\n- A therapist can help them develop better communication skills\n\n6. Create peaceful environment\n- Promote positive interactions\n- Organize family activities that can help rebuild relationships\n\n7. Set boundaries\n- If arguments become aggressive, intervene to prevent escalation\n- Encourage respect and civility\n\n8. Take care of yourself\n- Don't let their conflict affect your mental health\n- Seek support from other family members or friends if needed\n\nRemember, you can't control their behavior, but you can help facilitate better understanding and communication.",
